      <description>Infrastructure update: Migrated from KaTeX to MathJax for math rendering. Although MathJax is a bit slower to load,1 it supports referencing numbered equations and linking to them.2
The following in markdown:
1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 $$ \begin{equation} \label{eq:1} C = W\log_{2} (1+\mathrm{SNR}) \end{equation} $$ See \eqref{eq:1}. will result in:
$$ \begin{equation} \label{eq:1} C = W\log_{2} (1+\mathrm{SNR}) \end{equation} $$
See \eqref{eq:1}.
If only I could somehow make Obsidian render the labeled equation without errors&amp;hellip;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Infrastructure update: Migrated from <a href="https://katex.org/">KaTeX</a> to <a href="https://www.mathjax.org/">MathJax</a> for math rendering. Although MathJax is a bit slower to load,<sup id="fnref:1"><a href="#fn:1" class="footnote-ref" role="doc-noteref">1</a></sup> it supports referencing numbered equations and linking to them.<sup id="fnref:2"><a href="#fn:2" class="footnote-ref" role="doc-noteref">2</a></sup></p>
<p>The following in markdown:</p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span><span class="lnt">2
</span><span class="lnt">3
</span><span class="lnt">4
</span><span class="lnt">5
</span><span class="lnt">6
</span><span class="lnt">7
</span><span class="lnt">8
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-latex" data-lang="latex"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="sb">$$</span><span class="nb">
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nb"></span><span class="nv">\begin</span><span class="nb">{equation}
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nb"></span><span class="nv">\label</span><span class="nb">{eq:</span><span class="m">1</span><span class="nb">}
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nb">C </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="nb"> W</span><span class="nv">\log</span><span class="nb">_{</span><span class="m">2</span><span class="nb">} </span><span class="o">(</span><span class="m">1</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="nv">\mathrm</span><span class="nb">{SNR}</span><span class="o">)</span><span class="nb">
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nb"></span><span class="nv">\end</span><span class="nb">{equation}
</span></span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="nb"></span><span class="s">$$</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"> 
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">See <span class="k">\eqref</span><span class="nb">{</span>eq:1<span class="nb">}</span>.
</span></span></code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div><p>will result in:</p>
<p>$$
\begin{equation}
\label{eq:1}
C = W\log_{2} (1+\mathrm{SNR})
\end{equation}
$$</p>
<p>See \eqref{eq:1}.</p>
<p>If only I could somehow make Obsidian render the labeled equation <a href="https://forum.obsidian.md/t/label-in-the-math-block-and-ref-in-the-content-at-the-same-time-cause-error/3189">without errors</a>&hellip;</p>
<div class="footnotes" role="doc-endnotes">
<hr>
<ol>
<li id="fn:1">
<p>See <a href="https://www.intmath.com/cg5/katex-mathjax-comparison.php">KaTeX and MathJax Comparison Demo</a>.&#160;<a href="#fnref:1" class="footnote-backref" role="doc-backlink">&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;</a></p>
</li>
<li id="fn:2">
<p><a href="https://ox-hugo.scripter.co/doc/equations/#mathjax-config-example">Equations — ox-hugo - Org to Hugo exporter</a>.&#160;<a href="#fnref:2" class="footnote-backref" role="doc-backlink">&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;</a></p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
]]></content:encoded>
